/* aether_world.iii -- III AETHER-WORLD: a live, resizable, mouse-driven 3D explorer of III's OWN sovereign geometry,
 * [APP-SURFACE-MODULE] -- window/app execution surface: compiled by its family gate so it cannot rot;
 * its unreached exports are app-class BY NATURE (headless corpus cannot pump a window) and are excluded
 * from the v3 dark census (mechanism: sanctus/corpus_coverage, reunification W0.2).
 * in III's OWN native window (raw Win32 + GDI, no toolkit, no library, no imported asset).
 *
 * It shows the actual calculus, not a demo:
 *   [1] PHOTONIC LATTICE + exact O_h geodesic  -- the crystal lattice nodes and the exact shortest photon route
 *       (photon_route::plr_bulk), drawn as the routed path of king-moves.  PHOTONS. LATTICE. LINES.
 *   [2] EXACT SHAPES + CSG  -- a sphere, an ellipsoid, and the EXACT sphere-minus-cylinder solid whose surface shell is
 *       decided point-by-point by csg_kernel::csg_inside (integer-exact membership).  ANY SHAPE.
 *   [3] WIREFRAME  -- a cube and an octahedron as edges + vertices.  LINES. CORNERS.
 * Coordinate axes always.  On-screen GDI labels say what you are looking at.
 *
 * Camera: DRAG to rotate, WHEEL to zoom, keys 1/2/3 to switch, R reset, Q/Esc quit.  The window is resizable/maximizable
 * (WS_OVERLAPPEDWINDOW + WM_SIZE) and the image fills the whole client.  Geometry is computed by III's exact organs; the
 * viewport projection is fixed-point integer for speed.  Ring R0.  Composes photon_route + csg_kernel. */
module aether_world

